    • Method Detail

      • getNextFromSource

        protected ETResponse<ETEvent> getNextFromSource()
        Retrieves a single eyetracking event from the RED-m eyetracker, wrapped in a ETResponse.

        If no new data is available, this method will return null as the responses data. NO_NEW_DATA_AVAILABLE indicates one of the following scenarios:

        • There is no new data available because the eyetracker has not computed new data yet
        • There is no new data available because a currently occurring fixation has not yet ended
        • The user is not fixating anything (eyes are moving too rapidly)
        • The users gaze is not in tracking range
        • The user is not properly tracked by the eyetracker

        If your eyetracking environment is properly set up, the most likely reason is that your application is polling faster than the eyetrackers refresh rate. Simply keep polling until a new event is registered, or introduce wait times between consecutive polls.

        Specified by:
        getNextFromSource in class ETReceiver<ETEvent>
        Returns:
        Eyetracking event
        Throws:
        ETException - If an error occured while retrieving a new event
        ETConnectionException - If no connection could be established to the eyetracker
